# MAX — AI FAQ Assistant

## Stack

- TypeScript strict mode, ESM modules (`import`/`export`, not `require`)
- Node 20+, pnpm workspaces
- Hono for HTTP, pg for Postgres, @xenova/transformers for embeddings
- No Prisma/Drizzle for now — raw SQL via `pg`
- No LangChain/LlamaIndex — write RAG pipeline directly

## Code style

- Prefer functions over classes unless state justifies it
- Named exports, avoid default exports
- Async/await, never raw promises with .then()
- Small focused modules over large files
- Error handling: throw typed errors, let them bubble to the top-level handler

## Comments

- Comment WHY, not WHAT
- No JSDoc on obvious functions
- Keep it sparse

## When making changes

- Don't rewrite code that wasn't asked to change
- If you see issues outside the task scope, mention them at the end, don't fix silently
- Ask before adding new dependencies
- Always show the commands to run (npm/pnpm, docker, psql) after code changes
